						<summary>

						<p>East wall of the Subramanya shrine in the Mukkaṇṭīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara; Raṅgarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1561, Pramādi, Kārttīka ba. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1639 A.D. November 14.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of a village (name not clear) as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> to god Mukkaṇṭīśvara at Kālavaguṉṭa by Daḷavāyi Tipānāyanayya.</p>						

